main event: Multiple military officers from the 67th Fighter Squadron reported sighting an unidentified object in the sky on 8 September 1949 at Clark Air Force Base in the Philippines. The object was observed climbing at a high rate of speed, leaving a con-trail, and then abruptly leveling off at high altitude.
interesting points: The object was observed climbing at a 30-degree angle at a high rate of speed, and it was estimated to have traveled well over 800 miles per hour.
Witnesses reported seeing a dark-colored object that was initially mistaken for a smoke trail, but was later identified as a con-trail which climbed at a 30-degree angle.
No physical evidence, photographs, or sketches of the object were obtained, and no evidence suggested that the object contacted the earth or came close to observing aircraft.
Radar sightings were not supported, and no evidence suggested possible releases of testing devices in the vicinity.
Winds aloft report indicated significant wind speeds at various altitudes, providing insight into the atmospheric conditions during the sighting.
sighted object: Unidentified object climbing at high speed, leaving a con-trail in the sky.
witnesses: Military officers from the 67th Fighter Squadron
